Notification API

A simple API for sending and managing notifications.

Definition

The Notification API provides endpoints to create notifications, deliver them through various channels, and track their status.
It is designed to be implementation-agnostic, allowing any backend, protocol, or storage system.

Core Concepts

Notification – A message intended for a recipient.

Channel – The delivery medium (e.g., email, SMS, push, etc.).

Status – The lifecycle state of a notification (queued, sent, delivered, failed).

Basic Endpoints

POST /notifications – Create and send a notification.

GET /notifications/{id} – Retrieve notification status